  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (ac07071 2023-03-26T00:04:24.930648335Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge test\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nThe bug occurs when trying to fork mainnet at a specific block. Nevertheless, it works correctly when the block number is not informed. I've run such tests in the past without any problems, so not sure why it crashes now.\r\n\r\nTest setup:\r\n\r\n```\r\nfunction setUp() public {\r\n        uint256 forkBlock = 16_900_000;\r\n        vm.createSelectFork(vm.rpcUrl(\"mainnet\"), forkBlock);\r\n        //vm.createSelectFork(vm.rpcUrl(\"mainnet\"));\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nbacktrace:\r\n```\r\nThe application panicked (crashed).\r\nMessage:  Integer overflow when casting to u32\r\nLocation: /home/runner/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/primitive-types-0.12.1/src/lib.rs:38\r\n\r\nThis is a bug. Consider reporting it at https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry\r\n\r\n  ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ BACKTRACE ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\r\n   1: start_thread<unknown>\r\n      at <unknown source file>:<unknown line>\r\n   2: clone<unknown>\r\n      at <unknown source file>:<unknown line>\r\n```\r\n\r\nPS: I'm using WSL in case that helps identify the root cause.",
